 maybe while your seas aren't rough enough, all I would say to you is,

889
00:54:11,000 --> 00:54:13,000
 "Look, we're not going to love you more if you agree with us,

890
00:54:13,000 --> 00:54:15,000
 and I'm just going to tell you that if you like what you got,

891
00:54:15,000 --> 00:54:18,000
 I encourage you to keep doing what you're doing, but I'm going to remind you,

892
00:54:18,000 --> 00:54:21,000
 if you keep doing what you're doing, you're not going to like what you got."

893
00:54:21,000 --> 00:54:26,000
 Because it's just a matter of time before you get low enough

894
00:54:26,000 --> 00:54:32,000
 that the pain's going to be intense enough that you're going to wonder

895
00:54:32,000 --> 00:54:33,000
 how in the world you got here.

896
00:54:33,000 --> 00:54:35,000
 You know, one of the things I do when everyone with my kids and we're out

897
00:54:35,000 --> 00:54:40,000
 and we come up across somebody that's living on the streets and we're asked to help them,

898
00:54:40,000 --> 00:54:42,000
 I always, "Man, tell me your name."

899
00:54:42,000 --> 00:54:44,000
 "My name's Todd. I introduced myself."

900
00:54:44,000 --> 00:54:45,000
 "Just go tell me your story."

901
00:54:46,000 --> 00:54:48,000
 "You want to hear my story?"

902
00:54:48,000 --> 00:54:49,000
 I go, "Yeah, man."

903
00:54:49,000 --> 00:54:50,000
 I have my kids right there with me.

904
00:54:50,000 --> 00:54:52,000
 I say, "Just tell us your story. How'd you end up here?"

905
00:54:52,000 --> 00:54:54,000
 And they always say the same thing.

906
00:54:54,000 --> 00:54:56,000
 They always go, "I'll tell you how I got here, man.

907
00:54:56,000 --> 00:55:01,000
 One bad decision at a time, and then another bad decision after that."

908
00:55:01,000 --> 00:55:07,000
 And I always ask them if they want to turn around those decisions,

909
00:55:07,000 --> 00:55:10,000
 or if they just want me to give them something that would give them strength

910
00:55:10,000 --> 00:55:19,000
 given their rebellion and their self-will and their despair and their wondering further.

911
00:55:19,000 --> 00:55:21,000
 And I go, "I'm not going to enable you in that, man."

912
00:55:21,000 --> 00:55:24,000
 The Bible's really clear in 2 Thessalonians 3.

913
00:55:24,000 --> 00:55:27,000
 It says, "If a man doesn't work, let his stomach work for him.

914
00:55:27,000 --> 00:55:29,000
 Let the pain of his circumstance go."

915
00:55:29,000 --> 00:55:33,000
 Hey, being lazy, being a slugger, being irresponsible, being addicted,

916
00:55:33,000 --> 00:55:36,000
 not taking opportunity to deal with my addiction and to find training

917
00:55:36,000 --> 00:55:39,000
 and to maybe be reparented and to start to work my way out.

918
00:55:39,000 --> 00:55:41,000
 Man, let your stomach work for him.

919
00:55:41,000 --> 00:55:45,000
 Sometimes God is not trying to pay you back, but he's trying to draw you back.

920
00:55:45,000 --> 00:55:47,000
 And what you don't want to do is keep enabling people.

921
00:55:47,000 --> 00:55:51,000
 You also don't want to look at those people and think, "Man, what a scourge of the earth.

922
00:55:51,000 --> 00:55:55,000
 I look at them, and I just go, 'Hey, I really understand.

923
00:55:55,000 --> 00:55:57,000
 I was with one of those guys today.'

924
00:55:57,000 --> 00:55:59,000
 And I just told them, 'Man, you're going to have to trust me.

925
00:55:59,000 --> 00:56:01,000
 I don't think I'm better than you.'

926
00:56:01,000 --> 00:56:04,000
 But by the grace of God, I've encountered truth maybe earlier in my life

927
00:56:04,000 --> 00:56:07,000
 than you're encountering it, and I've started to make decisions to walk with this God.

928
00:56:07,000 --> 00:56:09,000
 And that God wants to start to walk with you.

929
00:56:09,000 --> 00:56:11,000
 And if you'll let me, I'll begin to walk with you.

930
00:56:11,000 --> 00:56:14,000
 We'll get shelter. We'll get training. We'll get food. We'll get provision.

931
00:56:14,000 --> 00:56:21,000
 And I'll let you know the God that keeps me from bringing despair to my heart on the streets."

932
00:56:21,000 --> 00:56:24,000
 This particular friend wasn't ready yet.

933
00:56:24,000 --> 00:56:27,000
 So we had a great conversation, and I said, "Bro, if you like what you got,

934
00:56:27,000 --> 00:56:28,000
 keep doing what you're doing.

935
00:56:28,000 --> 00:56:36,000
 But if you keep doing what you're doing, you're not going to like what you got."

936
00:56:36,000 --> 00:56:41,000
 Thirdly, there's people who are saved, and they don't act like it.

937
00:56:41,000 --> 00:56:43,000
 There's folks that are lost, and they know it.

938
00:56:43,000 --> 00:56:44,000
 To you, I say, "Come."

939
00:56:44,000 --> 00:56:47,000
 There's folks that are lost, and they don't think they're lost,

940
00:56:47,000 --> 00:56:49,000
 and they like the way they're sailing, but say, "You keep sailing."

941
00:56:49,000 --> 00:56:52,000
 And when the seas get rough enough, I hope you remember tonight's message.

942
00:56:52,000 --> 00:56:55,000
 There's somebody who's been thrown in the sea for you to make it calm.

943
00:56:55,000 --> 00:57:01,000
 But then there's some people that have been saved, and they don't sail like it.

944
00:57:01,000 --> 00:57:05,000
 And to you, I wanted to tell you, man, when you are given the Word of God,

945
00:57:05,000 --> 00:57:10,000
 and you don't deal to it kindly, you better check to see if you even know about the love of God.

946
00:57:10,000 --> 00:57:13,000
 Because people that really know the love of God, when they see it, they make a vow.

947
00:57:13,000 --> 00:57:15,000
 And they go, "I'm going to respond to that love.

948
00:57:15,000 --> 00:57:23,000
 I'm not going to try and earn it, but I see that love, and that love compels me."

949
00:57:23,000 --> 00:57:25,000
 And I want to just remind you of that earlier story.

950
00:57:25,000 --> 00:57:27,000
 What about those people who have never heard?

951
00:57:27,000 --> 00:57:29,000
 Well, I'm not so concerned about that person who's never heard.

952
00:57:29,000 --> 00:57:31,000
 A better question is, what about those who have heard

953
00:57:31,000 --> 00:57:35,000
 and don't care to share that, what we have heard, with others?

954
00:57:35,000 --> 00:57:39,000
 Can we really have heard?

955
00:57:39,000 --> 00:57:41,000
 And then there's the fourth group.

956
00:57:41,000 --> 00:57:48,000
 It's those who have really heard the Word of the Lord, and they're serving.

957
00:57:48,000 --> 00:57:51,000
 And they're out there, and they're faithful.

958
00:57:51,000 --> 00:57:53,000
 And they don't look at others like they're Ninevites,

959
00:57:53,000 --> 00:57:55,000
 and man, may the grace of God not come to them.

960
00:57:55,000 --> 00:57:56,000
 No, they really love them.

961
00:57:56,000 --> 00:57:58,000
 I want to tell you a story of a guy I was just with.

962
00:57:58,000 --> 00:58:02,000
 I just got back from Turkey and Eurasia and that general region,

963
00:58:02,000 --> 00:58:08,000
 and I was talking to a friend of mine that is a former imam in Jordan.

964
00:58:08,000 --> 00:58:13,000
 He was a particular guy that was rowing and rowing and rowing and rowing as an imam.

965
00:58:13,000 --> 00:58:15,000
 He said, "I was ready to die for Allah.

966
00:58:15,000 --> 00:58:19,000
 I was planning to give my life on a suicide mission for Allah

967
00:58:19,000 --> 00:58:22,000
 because I knew that was the only way that I could earn Allah's love

968
00:58:22,000 --> 00:58:25,000
 in this system invented by men."

969
00:58:25,000 --> 00:58:32,000
 And the systems of men are always, "Row your way to peace with Allah."

970
00:58:32,000 --> 00:58:35,000
 And he said, "And I saw the futility of this,

971
00:58:35,000 --> 00:58:38,000
 and eventually before I killed myself, I died to the idea."

972
00:58:38,000 --> 00:58:41,000
 And he said, "I became an atheist, and as soon as I left Islam,

973
00:58:41,000 --> 00:58:43,000
 becoming an imam, I didn't trust anything else,

974
00:58:43,000 --> 00:58:49,000
 but because I no longer served Allah, men started to want to kill me."

975
00:58:49,000 --> 00:58:55,000
 I had another friend who had come to understand that a prophet had been given for them.

976
00:58:55,000 --> 00:58:58,000
 That there was a God that didn't want you to earn His love,

977
00:58:58,000 --> 00:59:01,000
 but there was a God that loved you.

978
00:59:01,000 --> 00:59:04,000
 Do you know in Islam, there's 99 names for Allah.

979
00:59:04,000 --> 00:59:07,000
 They're called the 99 beautiful names for the Lord.

980
00:59:07,000 --> 00:59:10,000
 That's what Allah means in Arabic.

981
00:59:10,000 --> 00:59:14,000
 And not a single one of those 99 names that represent Allah

982
00:59:14,000 --> 00:59:18,000
 have the idea of love in them.

983
00:59:18,000 --> 00:59:24,000
 And this friend told him about a God who said, "He is love."

984
00:59:24,000 --> 00:59:28,000
 And he demonstrated his love in that while we're still rowing,

985
00:59:28,000 --> 00:59:30,000
 most of us in a disobedient direction,

986
00:59:30,000 --> 00:59:34,000
 He died for us, and He made provision for us.

987
00:59:34,000 --> 00:59:37,000
 Because He's just, and in no means will He let the guilty go unpunished,

988
00:59:37,000 --> 00:59:40,000
 but He Himself has given His life for them,

989
00:59:40,000 --> 00:59:44,000
 that He might be just and the justifier of those that He loves.

990
00:59:44,000 --> 00:59:46,000
 And he heard the story, and he wept.

991
00:59:46,000 --> 00:59:48,000
 And he left his atheism and he became a believer.

992
00:59:48,000 --> 00:59:52,000
 And then he came across one of his former Islamic friends,

993
00:59:52,000 --> 00:59:57,000
 who walked up behind him with a screwdriver and drove it through his back.

994
00:59:57,000 --> 01:00:00,000
 He felt the pain and he turned around, the man removed the screwdriver,

995
01:00:00,000 --> 01:00:04,000
 and shoved it in the front of his chest.

996
01:00:04,000 --> 01:00:07,000
 And pulled it out to stab him a third time,

997
01:00:07,000 --> 01:00:09,000
 and he grabbed his hands and he took his by the head,

998
01:00:09,000 --> 01:00:12,000
 and they were smashing, he was smashing his head

999
01:00:12,000 --> 01:00:14,000
 and the guy's weakness into the wall,

1000
01:00:14,000 --> 01:00:17,000
 and he just held on him screaming till somebody came and broke them up.

1001
01:00:17,000 --> 01:00:20,000
 Now in Jordan what they do when they see two men fighting,

1002
01:00:20,000 --> 01:00:22,000
 is they arrest them both.

1003
01:00:22,000 --> 01:00:24,000
 And so these two men were arrested.

1004
01:00:24,000 --> 01:00:27,000
 They stopped his hemorrhaging and bleeding, it missed all vital organs.

1005
01:00:27,000 --> 01:00:30,000
 He had a penetration through the back to the front,

1006
01:00:30,000 --> 01:00:32,000
 and from the front toward the back,

1007
01:00:32,000 --> 01:00:35,000
 and they put them in the same jail cell that evening.

1008
01:00:35,000 --> 01:00:38,000
 And while he was in that same jail cell,

1009
01:00:38,000 --> 01:00:41,000
 he looked at that man, they were both cuffed so they couldn't hurt each other,

1010
01:00:41,000 --> 01:00:45,000
 and he said, "I want you to know I don't hate you.

1011
01:00:45,000 --> 01:00:47,000
 "And I want you to know that if I live through this,

1012
01:00:47,000 --> 01:00:52,000
 "that my family's not going to try and strike revenge against you."

1013
01:00:52,000 --> 01:00:54,000
 The next day they were separated,

1014
01:00:54,000 --> 01:00:56,000
 they were asked to tell their story four different times.

1015
01:00:56,000 --> 01:00:58,000
 The man who was stabbed told the same story four times.

1016
01:00:58,000 --> 01:01:00,000
 The man who did the stabbing told four different stories,

1017
01:01:00,000 --> 01:01:03,000
 so they knew who was lying.

1018
01:01:03,000 --> 01:01:06,000
 And they were going to put this gentleman who had run the screwdriver

1019
01:01:06,000 --> 01:01:08,000
 through him front and back in prison,

1020
01:01:08,000 --> 01:01:10,000
 and he stood up, my friend, the former Irman,

1021
01:01:10,000 --> 01:01:12,000
 who was now a follower of the prophet,

1022
01:01:12,000 --> 01:01:14,000
 who was thrown into the sea for others,

1023
01:01:14,000 --> 01:01:16,000
 and he said, "Judge, if you will, I want to speak to the man who did this to me.

1024
01:01:16,000 --> 01:01:20,000
 "I want to say again to the court, I forgive you, and I forgive him.

1025
01:01:20,000 --> 01:01:24,000
 "And I love you, and I know you're doing what you think you should do

1026
01:01:24,000 --> 01:01:26,000
 "in order to please the God that you know,

1027
01:01:26,000 --> 01:01:28,000
 "but the God that you know is no God at all.

1028
01:01:28,000 --> 01:01:30,000
 "The God you need to know is the God who gave his life for you,

1029
01:01:30,000 --> 01:01:32,000
 "and he gave his life for me,

1030
01:01:32,000 --> 01:01:34,000
 "and if he was willing to save one such as me,

1031
01:01:34,000 --> 01:01:39,000
 "he's willing for me to forgive one such as you."

1032
01:01:39,000 --> 01:01:40,000
 And that man looked at him and said,

1033
01:01:40,000 --> 01:01:42,000
 "Now I know that your God is the one true God

1034
01:01:42,000 --> 01:01:44,000
 "because I've never seen love like that."

1035
01:01:44,000 --> 01:01:52,000
 That's what people who have come to know the kindness of God do.

1036
01:01:52,000 --> 01:01:55,000
 If you have received the word of the Lord, having received it,

1037
01:01:55,000 --> 01:01:57,000
 there is an obligation to share it.

1038
01:01:57,000 --> 01:01:59,000
 I love this little poem. It always encourages me.

1039
01:01:59,000 --> 01:02:00,000
 It goes like this. It's called "My Friend."

1040
01:02:00,000 --> 01:02:02,000
 It says, "My friend, I stand in judgment now

1041
01:02:02,000 --> 01:02:04,000
 "and feel that you're to blame somehow.

1042
01:02:04,000 --> 01:02:06,000
 "On earth I walked with you day by day.

1043
01:02:06,000 --> 01:02:08,000
 "Never did you point me the way.

1044
01:02:08,000 --> 01:02:10,000
 "You knew the Lord in truth and glory,

1045
01:02:10,000 --> 01:02:12,000
 "but never did you tell me the story.

1046
01:02:12,000 --> 01:02:14,000
 "My knowledge then was very dim.

1047
01:02:14,000 --> 01:02:16,000
 "You could have led me straight to him.

1048
01:02:16,000 --> 01:02:18,000
 "Though we lived together on earth,

1049
01:02:18,000 --> 01:02:20,000
 "you never told me of the second birth,

1050
01:02:20,000 --> 01:02:21,000
 "and now I stand to stay condemned

1051
01:02:21,000 --> 01:02:24,000
 "because you failed to mention him.

1052
01:02:24,000 --> 01:02:26,000
 "You taught me many things, that's true.

1053
01:02:26,000 --> 01:02:27,000
 "I called you friend and trusted you,

1054
01:02:27,000 --> 01:02:29,000
 "but I learn now that it's too late.

1055
01:02:29,000 --> 01:02:31,000
 "You could have saved me from this fate.

1056
01:02:31,000 --> 01:02:33,000
 "We walked by day, we talked by night,

1057
01:02:33,000 --> 01:02:35,000
 "and yet you showed me not the light.

1058
01:02:35,000 --> 01:02:36,000
 "You let me live and love and die.

1059
01:02:36,000 --> 01:02:38,000
 "You knew I'd never live on high.

1060
01:02:38,000 --> 01:02:41,000
 "Yes, I called you friend in life

1061
01:02:41,000 --> 01:02:43,000
 "and laughed with you through joy and stripe,

1062
01:02:43,000 --> 01:02:44,000
 "and yet on coming to the end,

1063
01:02:44,000 --> 01:02:51,000
 "I cannot call you now my friend,

1064
01:02:51,000 --> 01:02:53,000
 "because you didn't want to go through the awkwardness

1065
01:02:53,000 --> 01:02:56,000
 "of telling me that you believe that God threw a prophet

1066
01:02:56,000 --> 01:02:57,000
 "in the sea of judgment for you

1067
01:02:57,000 --> 01:03:04,000
 "because you thought it would make me think you were crazy."

1068
01:03:04,000 --> 01:03:05,000
 See, man, this is what prophets do.

1069
01:03:05,000 --> 01:03:07,000
 People who are really saved and act like they're saved

1070
01:03:07,000 --> 01:03:08,000
 are a blessing to others.

1071
01:03:08,000 --> 01:03:14,000
 They realize that they were blessed to be a blessing.

1072
01:03:14,000 --> 01:03:15,000
 Can I just close this by telling you

1073
01:03:15,000 --> 01:03:18,000
 that there's another one who was a prophet

1074
01:03:18,000 --> 01:03:20,000
 who was from Kephir Nahum.

1075
01:03:20,000 --> 01:03:21,000
 Capernaum is the town.

1076
01:03:21,000 --> 01:03:23,000
 It means the village of comfort.

1077
01:03:23,000 --> 01:03:25,000
 Just like there was a prophet, Nahum,

1078
01:03:25,000 --> 01:03:28,000
 that was sent to the Assyrians who worshiped the fish god

1079
01:03:28,000 --> 01:03:30,000
 that God had once swallowed up by a great fish

1080
01:03:30,000 --> 01:03:34,000
 that was spit out probably with some sort of lactic acid

1081
01:03:34,000 --> 01:03:36,000
 all over him so he was bleached white,

1082
01:03:36,000 --> 01:03:38,000
 and so here comes this guy spit up on the fish,

1083
01:03:38,000 --> 01:03:44,000
 looked like a ghost, preaching reconciliation with God.

1084
01:03:44,000 --> 01:03:47,000
 They might have listened to that message.

1085
01:03:47,000 --> 01:03:49,000
 In other words, his life was radically changed

1086
01:03:49,000 --> 01:03:50,000
 and he carried a message of power.

1087
01:03:50,000 --> 01:03:53,000
 So should yours.

1088
01:03:53,000 --> 01:03:55,000
 If you're really saved, you start to become that one.

1089
01:03:55,000 --> 01:03:57,000
 When Jesus was here, he was exactly that.

1090
01:03:57,000 --> 01:04:00,000
 He said if you don't believe my words, believe my walk.

1091
01:04:00,000 --> 01:04:01,000
 They said well show us some more signs.

1092
01:04:01,000 --> 01:04:06,000
 He said there's no more signs except the sign of Jonah.

1093
01:04:06,000 --> 01:04:11,000
 When I'm swallowed up, if you will, for three days

1094
01:04:11,000 --> 01:04:13,000
 in what looks like certain death, only to live again

1095
01:04:13,000 --> 01:04:15,000
 from which I will pronounce to you one more time,

1096
01:04:15,000 --> 01:04:21,000
 I am the way, the truth, and the life.

1097
01:04:21,000 --> 01:04:25,000
 See I don't know what you worship, but I'm gonna tell you

1098
01:04:25,000 --> 01:04:28,000
 that when you see a God defeat your great enemy death

1099
01:04:28,000 --> 01:04:33,000
 and he returns and tells you I did this for you,

1100
01:04:33,000 --> 01:04:35,000
 that's not just some story in history,

1101
01:04:35,000 --> 01:04:38,000
 it is the pivot point of your eternity.

1102
01:04:38,000 --> 01:04:40,000
 And what you do with that prophet who was thrown

1103
01:04:40,000 --> 01:04:42,000
 in the sea of judgment for you will determine

1104
01:04:42,000 --> 01:04:43,000
 where you spend it.

1105
01:04:43,000 --> 01:04:45,000
 And if you know him, you will make a vow to love him

1106
01:04:45,000 --> 01:04:47,000
 the way he gave his life for you.

1107
01:04:47,000 --> 01:04:50,000
 And part of that is having received that word

1108
01:04:50,000 --> 01:04:55,000
 is to gladly share it with others.

1109
01:04:55,000 --> 01:04:57,000
 And so this story that happened before Christ

1110
01:04:57,000 --> 01:04:59,000
 anticipates Christ and the story about Christ

1111
01:04:59,000 --> 01:05:01,000
 anticipates that you should respond to it

1112
01:05:01,000 --> 01:05:05,000
 and you should join Christ in suffering in every way

1113
01:05:05,000 --> 01:05:07,000
 that you need to so that the world might know

1114
01:05:07,000 --> 01:05:10,000
 you died to yourself, that Christ might live in you

1115
01:05:10,000 --> 01:05:14,000
 and his message might go forth and his power might be seen

1116
01:05:14,000 --> 01:05:19,000
 so the Ninevites could be free.

1117
01:05:19,000 --> 01:05:21,000
 Father I pray if there's any Ninevites in the room,

1118
01:05:21,000 --> 01:05:25,000
 folks who came in here that are living lives of terror,

1119
01:05:25,000 --> 01:05:28,000
 that maybe are in rooms in Houston and Fort Worth

1120
01:05:28,000 --> 01:05:30,000
 and in Dallas and other places watching around the world

1121
01:05:30,000 --> 01:05:35,000
 tonight that all they seek to do is to live in rebellion

1122
01:05:35,000 --> 01:05:38,000
 against God and to bring others into their powers

1123
01:05:38,000 --> 01:05:41,000
 and into their patterns so that they can have sway

1124
01:05:41,000 --> 01:05:45,000
 over them and use them for their own pleasure.

1125
01:05:45,000 --> 01:05:47,000
 And Lord we don't look at any of the people that are here

1126
01:05:47,000 --> 01:05:49,000
 and listen to this message like we're better than them.

1127
01:05:49,000 --> 01:05:52,000
 That's the way we would have sailed unless grace came to us,

1128
01:05:52,000 --> 01:05:54,000
 unless the great prophet convinced us that there was

1129
01:05:54,000 --> 01:05:57,000
 a better way and showed us love, that he gave his life for us,

1130
01:05:57,000 --> 01:05:59,000
 that we might be reconciled to you in goodness

1131
01:05:59,000 --> 01:06:04,000
 so that we could start to sail towards safe harbors

1132
01:06:04,000 --> 01:06:07,000
 filled with hope and with song.

1133
01:06:07,000 --> 01:06:10,000
 So Lord we thank you just for this story in history,

1134
01:06:10,000 --> 01:06:14,000
 the way you seek after rebels.

1135
01:06:14,000 --> 01:06:18,000
 We thank you that that story anticipates the great prophet

1136
01:06:18,000 --> 01:06:23,000
 who gave his perfect life for the Ninevites like me.

1137
01:06:23,000 --> 01:06:26,000
 That I would stop rowing towards you to try and earn my way

1138
01:06:26,000 --> 01:06:29,000
 and I would receive the gift of your sacrifice

1139
01:06:29,000 --> 01:06:32,000
 that I might live.

1140
01:06:32,000 --> 01:06:34,000
 So Lord help me now having seen your great love,

1141
01:06:34,000 --> 01:06:36,000
 me to make a vow to try and respond to it.

1142
01:06:36,000 --> 01:06:38,000
 Thank you that even my imperfection in responding to that,

1143
01:06:38,000 --> 01:06:40,000
 your grace is sufficient.

1144
01:06:40,000 --> 01:06:43,000
 But Lord I want to learn more of your ways.

1145
01:06:43,000 --> 01:06:46,000
 I pray that my life would be as shockingly different

1146
01:06:46,000 --> 01:06:49,000
 as Jonas must have been when he was regurgitated

1147
01:06:49,000 --> 01:06:52,000
 from the belly of a whale for three days.

1148
01:06:52,000 --> 01:06:55,000
 That people would see that I've come from someplace else,

1149
01:06:55,000 --> 01:06:58,000
 sent forth from you, living in righteousness,

1150
01:06:58,000 --> 01:07:02,000
 sanctified by your work of deliverance.

1151
01:07:02,000 --> 01:07:05,000
 With a mouth filled with kindness and grace,

1152
01:07:05,000 --> 01:07:07,000
 speaking of the glories and goodness of who you are,

1153
01:07:07,000 --> 01:07:09,000
 not who I am.

1154
01:07:09,000 --> 01:07:11,000
 Realizing that the only reason I'm a prophet is because

1155
01:07:11,000 --> 01:07:14,000
 I've received from you what I freely offer to others.

1156
01:07:14,000 --> 01:07:16,000
 I pray Lord for people who really know you in this room,

1157
01:07:16,000 --> 01:07:18,000
 that we would not sail on our own,

1158
01:07:18,000 --> 01:07:19,000
 but we would go where you tell us to go

1159
01:07:19,000 --> 01:07:21,000
 and live as you tell us to live.

1160
01:07:21,000 --> 01:07:24,000
 In humility, faithfulness, and love.

1161
01:07:24,000 --> 01:07:28,000
 Thank you that this room is filled with such men and women.

1162
01:07:28,000 --> 01:07:31,000
 Thank you tonight that more can come.

1163
01:07:31,000 --> 01:07:38,000
 If they just say I'm sick and tired of being sick and tired.

1164
01:07:38,000 --> 01:07:42,000
 I thank you that you gave your life for me.

1165
01:07:42,000 --> 01:07:45,000
 I thank you that the sacrifice of your son

1166
01:07:45,000 --> 01:07:50,000
 calmed the seas of judgment due me.

1167
01:07:50,000 --> 01:07:53,000
 I thank you Father that you raised him from that sea of judgment

1168
01:07:53,000 --> 01:07:56,000
 as evidence that your wrath had been satisfied

1169
01:07:56,000 --> 01:07:59,000
 and my debt has been paid.

1170
01:07:59,000 --> 01:08:02,000
 And I pray that that power that resurrected him from the grave

1171
01:08:02,000 --> 01:08:05,000
 as a sign of your grace would live in me

1172
01:08:05,000 --> 01:08:10,000
 as I walk with you for the good of others

1173
01:08:10,000 --> 01:08:16,000
 as I sing songs of redemption to Assyrians and prophets alike.

1174
01:08:16,000 --> 01:08:19,000
 Lord would you help us to walk with you.

1175
01:08:19,000 --> 01:08:22,000
 Would you let us live in that grace in Jesus name.

1176
01:08:22,000 --> 01:08:24,000
 Amen.

1177
01:08:24,000 --> 01:08:28,000
 Well man if that song is the cry of your heart

1178
01:08:28,000 --> 01:08:30,000
 then you're in a really good place.

1179
01:08:30,000 --> 01:08:32,000
 (laughter)

1180
01:08:32,000 --> 01:08:34,000
 (applause)

1181
01:08:34,000 --> 01:08:36,000
 Thank you.

1182
01:08:36,000 --> 01:08:39,000
 Yeah let me just tell you and remind you about that picture.

1183
01:08:39,000 --> 01:08:41,000
 I didn't see that thing.

1184
01:08:41,000 --> 01:08:42,000
 Put it back up there.

1185
01:08:42,000 --> 01:08:45,000
 I didn't see that thing.

1186
01:08:45,000 --> 01:08:48,000
 And what's amazing is some of you guys think you're in a good place maybe

1187
01:08:48,000 --> 01:08:49,000
 and you don't want the Lord to take over yet.

1188
01:08:49,000 --> 01:08:50,000
 You think you just swim in the ocean.

1189
01:08:50,000 --> 01:08:52,000
 There's no monster here that can swallow me up.

1190
01:08:52,000 --> 01:08:53,000
 This is all good.

1191
01:08:53,000 --> 01:08:57,000
 And you don't even know what's right there next to you.

1192
01:08:57,000 --> 01:09:00,000
 And God in his kindness one day

1193
01:09:00,000 --> 01:09:03,000
 if you're blessed because the Lord disciplines his children

1194
01:09:03,000 --> 01:09:05,000
 and those he loves you're going to find yourself in the belly of a whale.

1195
01:09:05,000 --> 01:09:08,000
 And if you're not ready to respond tonight I pray you respond then.

1196
01:09:08,000 --> 01:09:10,000
 I pray you know that God's not mad at you.

1197
01:09:10,000 --> 01:09:12,000
 That he's not putting you in the belly of a whale because he's punishing you.

1198
01:09:12,000 --> 01:09:14,000
 That's just what happens when you swim in a sea

1199
01:09:14,000 --> 01:09:16,000
 where there are monsters that lurk.

1200
01:09:16,000 --> 01:09:18,000
 And anytime you're not sailing with him you need to know

1201
01:09:18,000 --> 01:09:23,000
 there are monsters in that ocean that can swallow you easily.

1202
01:09:23,000 --> 01:09:27,000
 And God's always ready to hear your prayer.

1203
01:09:27,000 --> 01:09:29,000
 But today is the day of salvation.

1204
01:09:29,000 --> 01:09:30,000
 Let us cry to God

1205
01:09:30,000 --> 01:09:35,000
 because in a flood of great waters he may not always be found.

1206
01:09:35,000 --> 01:09:37,000
 But if you cry to him tonight

1207
01:09:37,000 --> 01:09:39,000
 and you say take over lover of my soul

1208
01:09:39,000 --> 01:09:41,000
 that you would throw yourself in the ocean

1209
01:09:41,000 --> 01:09:46,000
 that I might be free.

1210
01:09:46,000 --> 01:09:48,000
 He says just come.

1211
01:09:48,000 --> 01:09:50,000
 And if you have come and you know him

1212
01:09:50,000 --> 01:09:52,000
 then would you just go faithfully?

1213
01:09:52,000 --> 01:09:54,000
 Would you go and tell others unashamedly and boldly?

1214
01:09:54,000 --> 01:09:56,000
 Would you live and would you suffer for them?

1215
01:09:56,000 --> 01:09:58,000
 Would you go into their Nineveh and declare?

1216
01:09:58,000 --> 01:10:00,000
 Don't go and mingle with the Ninevites.

1217
01:10:00,000 --> 01:10:02,000
 You've got to be distinct and different.

1218
01:10:02,000 --> 01:10:04,000
 As one raised from the dead

1219
01:10:04,000 --> 01:10:06,000
 clothed in righteousness

1220
01:10:06,000 --> 01:10:08,000
 declaring to them the reason

1221
01:10:08,000 --> 01:10:13,000
 for your otherworldly appearance.

1222
01:10:13,000 --> 01:10:14,000
 With freedom.

1223
01:10:14,000 --> 01:10:16,000
 Not performing so God would accept you

1224
01:10:16,000 --> 01:10:18,000
 but out of his acceptance

1225
01:10:18,000 --> 01:10:20,000
 responding in love.

1226
01:10:20,000 --> 01:10:22,000
 Would you come if you don't know him?

1227
01:10:22,000 --> 01:10:23,000
 Let him take over.

1228
01:10:23,000 --> 01:10:25,000
 And would you go if he's taken over with you?

1229
01:10:25,000 --> 01:10:27,000
 If you're here and you're headed to launch

1230
01:10:27,000 --> 01:10:29,000
 and you want to serve others at launch

1231
01:10:29,000 --> 01:10:31,000
 and head up to the loft and jump into our leaders meeting

1232
01:10:31,000 --> 01:10:33,000
 and if you're in other towns

1233
01:10:33,000 --> 01:10:35,000
 there's opportunities for you to serve there.

1234
01:10:35,000 --> 01:10:36,000
 Connect with your leaders.

1235
01:10:36,000 --> 01:10:38,000
 Come.

1236
01:10:38,000 --> 01:10:40,000
 Go.

1237
01:10:40,000 --> 01:10:42,000
 Worship the King who gave himself for you.

1238
01:10:42,000 --> 01:10:44,000
 In Jesus' name be free.

1239
01:10:44,000 --> 01:10:46,000
 Bless you.

